Book Ordering Flow
Tanvir Raju
The product:
A website where user can order various types of
categorized books through an easy to experience
ordering flow for upcoming wants.
Project overview
Project duration:
15/1/2023-Current
The problem:
Ordering various types of books for
appropriate wants through an easy to user
experience.
Project overview
The goal:
Develop an easy to user experience ordering
flow so that the users can order books various
types of categories.
My role:
UX designer, UX researcher, etc.

User research: summary
I have conducted various moderate and un-moderate researches on how to improve the books
ordering flow ux. The research interviews included various range of users who love to browse and
select the specific books based on needs. They all tend to expect the book ordering flow to be
more user simple, friendly and easier to use.
User research: pain points

Takeaways
Next steps
Going forward
Takeaways
Impact:
Users shared that the app made book ordering
flow seem like something they could actually
help simplify. One quote from peer feedback
was that the book ordering flow needs to
simplified as soon as possible.
What I learned:
I learned that even though the problem I was
trying to solve was a big one, diligently going
through each step of the design process and
aligning with specific user needs helped me
come up with solutions that were both feasible
and useful.
Next steps
Conduct research on how
successful the app is in
reaching the goal to
simplify book ordering
flow.
Add more educational
resources for users to
learn about book
ordering.
Provide incentives and
rewards to users for
successfully completed
book ordering process.
